**The Index Luke**
Use The Index, Luke is a free online resource that teaches SQL indexing and performance tuning for developers.
It explains how indexes work and how to write efficient queries across databases like MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, and SQL Server.

Link: https://use-the-index-luke.com/

**The NewYork times**
jobs.nytimes.com is The New York Times’ official job board hosting curated job listings across industries.
You’ll find roles in journalism, tech, business, and corporate functions with direct postings from employers.
It’s useful if you’re targeting reputable companies and a mix of specialized and general career opportunities.

Link: https://jobs.nytimes.com/



